1
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:13,600
Yaoyao.

2
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:17,080
Yaoyao.

3
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:21,560
Don't you think this guy is really weird? Where exactly are you taking me?

4
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:22,280
It's fine.

5
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,480
Just trust me.

6
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:24,880
Trust my intuition.

7
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:26,080
Please stay with me.

8
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:28,500
What do you want to eat?

9
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:35,759
Let's eat here.

10
00:01:35,759 --> 00:01:36,360
Let's go.

11
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:46,840
Boss.

12
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,640
Welcome.

13
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:50,770
What would the three of you like to eat?

14
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,360
Any recommendations?

15
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:54,240
Here's the menu.

16
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:56,160
Everything is good. Order whatever you like.

17
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,360
Then we'll have this,

18
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,960
this,

19
00:01:58,960 --> 00:01:59,800
and a soup.

20
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:00,360
Okay.

21
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:00,760
Thanks.

22
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,600
Do you have rice?

23
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:02,800
Yes. All you can eat.

24
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:11,120
Yaoyao,

25
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,840
do you smell a weird smell?

26
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,200
I do. What about it?

27
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,600
We don't even know this guy,

28
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:18,930
and there's this smell.

29
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,560
What kind of meal is this?

30
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,600
Besides,

31
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,860
didn't we agree to eat street food today?

32
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,960
Meeting this kind of person is a rare opportunity.

33
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,410
This kind of person?

34
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,400
Ah.

35
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:32,640
Just play along.

36
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:35,040
I'll treat you to a late-night snack later.

37
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:35,760
You are like this,

38
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,480
I am like this,

39
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:37,200
okay?

40
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,480
Grandpa.

41
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,010
Listening to the radio?

42
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,260
What are you listening to?

43
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,800
Ah, this doesn't sound good.

44
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,400
Change it.

45
00:02:57,079 --> 00:02:58,200
Okay, this is good.

46
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,240
What is this?

47
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,000
Disney?

48
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:03,880
Dum-dum-dum-dum.

49
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:14,200
Have you finished your homework?

50
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,160
Watching this stuff...

51
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,560
Go check on your sister.

52
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:29,660
You guys... long-distance transport must be exhausting.

53
00:03:31,079 --> 00:03:32,160
I have a mission.

54
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,680
It's not exhausting.

55
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,040
Mission?

56
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:36,800
What mission?

57
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:39,010
A transportation mission.

58
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,240
In the 28th year of the Republic of China,

59
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,240
answering the call of the China Relief General Association,

60
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,880
our first batch of Southeast Asian mechanics

61
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,960
was responsible for transporting supplies

62
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,760
from Lashio to Kunming to support the front lines.

63
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:52,560
The 28th year of the Republic of China.

64
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,220
It was the Anti-Japanese War.

65
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:59,290
As of today, I've been back in China for exactly three years.

66
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:03,960
Are you telling a time-travel story?

67
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,760
Food is here.

68
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:20,959
Here it is.

69
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:31,640
Enjoy your meal.

70
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,300
Order more if it's not enough.

71
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,360
Is there something wrong with his head?

72
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,200
Stop it.

73
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,000
Yaoyao.

74
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,360
Didn't you hear him?

75
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:14,480
He just mentioned the Republic of China.

76
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,280
That's from my great-grandfather's generation.

77
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,440
Great-grandfather?

78
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,080
She's right.

79
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:24,160
1939 is already several generations ago.

80
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:49,280
But where exactly am I now?

81
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,840
Boss, how much is this meal?

82
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,360
This meal is on us.

83
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,720
Oh, I can't accept that.

84
00:05:59,000 --> 00:05:59,920
That's it.

85
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,960
It's on us.

86
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,420
You can treat us next time.

87
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,440
Then my ID...

88
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,360
Here you go.

89
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,480
Then thank you both.

90
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,160
But I still have important duties.

91
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,290
Until we meet again.

92
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,600
Hey.

93
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,159
Come again next time!

94
00:06:43,159 --> 00:06:44,240
Boss, more rice!

95
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,240
Okay, getting it for you right away.

96
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,440
Wife, why is the rice gone?

97
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:53,000
You said all-you-can-eat rice.

98
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,040
That guy just ate it all.

99
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:57,800
Sorry.

100
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,680
Wait a moment.

101
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,210
New rice will be ready soon.

102
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,480
He licked the bowl cleaner than I could wash it.

103
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:08,970
The 28th year of the Republic of China.

104
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,080
Honey,

105
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:13,940
which year is the 28th year of the Republic of China?

106
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,040
How should I know?

107
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,560
It was 1939.

108
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:24,240
Yaoyao, are we going to keep doing this?

109
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,640
Nanyang Volunteers.

110
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,600
It's in the overseas Chinese archives.

111
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,640
I want to know more about this story.

112
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,280
There are so many stories like this.

113
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,200
If anyone wears these clothes

114
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:36,000
and says they are from here or there,

115
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,080
do you want to learn about them

116
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,400
and buy them a meal too?

117
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,320
No, he's different.

118
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,000
I trust my instincts.

119
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,720
Did you notice?

120
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:48,320
From meeting him to the pharmacy and then to eating just now,

121
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,850
besides that volunteer ID,

122
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,840
he never took out a phone.

123
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,640
Neither a watch nor earphones.

124
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,570
He has nothing modern on him at all.

125
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,120
So what?

126
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,280
Is he really a great time traveler?

127
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,400
Let me tell you.

128
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,480
Like him,

129
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,000
playing a gentle homeless person,

130
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,600
there are plenty of actors.

131
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,880
What does it prove?

132
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:11,340
He wouldn't have such feelings without personal experience.

133
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:14,040
Besides, the Nanyang Volunteers,

134
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,700
I've never even heard of them.

135
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,440
Look.

136
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,000
Yaoyao.

137
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:23,600
Do you really believe he time-traveled from the Republic of China?

138
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,200
That's really absurd.

139
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:27,200
There are many absurd things.

140
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,730
But there is only one truth.

141
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:30,680
Lin Yaozu, please wait a moment.

142
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,720
It's you two again.

143
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,850
What can I do for you?

144
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,120
Do for you?

145
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,039
Are you shooting a prank show?

146
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:41,679
Where are the cameras?

147
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:43,400
Where are your cameras?

148
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:45,440
Don't talk nonsense.

149
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,120
She doesn't mean that.

150
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,200
What nonsense?

151
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:53,160
The smell on your body

152
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:54,800
makes me dizzy.

153
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:56,720
Yes.

154
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:59,240
Indeed, I haven't taken a shower for a few days.

155
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:02,040
Taking a shower on the transport route is a luxury.

156
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:05,480
The smell is indeed a bit too much.

157
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,080
How about

158
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,920
you go to our place to wash up?

159
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:08,360
Go to your place?

160
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,220
Go to our place.

161
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:11,080
What are you afraid of?

162
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,340
Yaoyao, are you crazy?

163
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,400
No need.

164
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,680
I still need to find my car.

165
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,920
Mr. Lin, look, it's starting to rain.

166
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:19,200
It's getting late.

167
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,930
Do you have a better choice?

168
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,280
Alright, alright.

169
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,720
I don't know what kind of magic

170
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:27,000
made this researcher so obsessed.

171
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,480
Let's go wash up.

172
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,080
I want to see

173
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,000
what else you can come up with after washing.

174
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,080
You are the best.

175
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,000
Let's go.

176
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,080
It's really hard to be a good person these days.
